{
  "style": "",
  "texts": [
    "The hash values of transactions are extracted.",
    "At each non-leaf node, the hash values of the child nodes are combined and the hash of that node is extracted, as expressed in the following equation:Hash 01 ¼ HashðHash 0 þ Hash 1 ÞThis process continues until the root node.",
    "The hash value of the root node is the validation of all transactions.When any transaction on the tree is changed, its hash value also changes, and then, all the hash values on the path from it to the root node will change.",
    "The validation process will fail when the root node hash has changed.",
    "The Merkle tree allows for secure and efficient validation of big data structures."
  ],
  "correct_citations": []
}